  "body": "`Part of #9264 keycard sign-in epic (mark as checked there, when closing this issue)`\r\n\r\nOn the sign in screen:\r\n- For  accessing key, the button label copy should be \"Access key\" whereas its \"Recover key\" currently;\r\n- The \"Access key\" button should be in a footer with a 1px top border. This footer should stick to the bottom regardless of the size of the device screen;\r\n- Tap on \"Access key\" should open a dropdown with two options: \r\n  1. Enter seed phrase (Go to the relevant flow accordingly);\r\n  2. Access with Keycard (Go to the relevant flow accordingly);\r\n- On smaller screens, the footer should shrink according to spec below\r\n\r\n\r\nImages:\r\n<img width=\"800\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019-10-28 at 15 25 12\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67659399-281edd00-f997-11e9-9a32-046a18319268.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"919\" alt=\"accerss\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67829138-f467c280-fb10-11e9-9fc8-f7109b803612.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n<img width=\"773\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019-10-28 at 15 16 03\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67658879-df1a5900-f995-11e9-98c6-159c1bb4eeae.png\">\r\n\r\nFigma:\r\nBig screens: https://www.figma.com/file/dEIljL7UPbXgsZUA0Q4qlE5E/Onboarding?node-id=4566%3A12\r\nSmall screens: https://www.figma.com/file/dEIljL7UPbXgsZUA0Q4qlE5E/Onboarding?node-id=5314%3A15\r\n\r\n",
